          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "COULX"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Electromagnetic excitation   of   oxygen   in",
                " heavy-ion  (18O + 208Pb) collisions.  To disentangle",
                " electromagnetic excitation from nuclear  interaction",
                " processes  the  fragment  mass  measured  with  good",
                " resolution was compared to the  number  of  neutrons",
                " emitted in the forward direction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High efficiency (~ 90 %) LAND neutron detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Direct measurement  of photoneutrons:  in the",
                " case  of electromagnetic excitation,  the difference",
                " in mass number  between the projectile and  fragment",
                " equals the number of neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The stable (18O) and unstable (20,22O) oxygen nuclei."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Reaction cross  section   determination   using   the",
                " measurements    of    numbers   of   neutrons   from",
                " electromagnetic  excitation  into  continuum   (from",
                " fragment   mass   measurement)  and  of  numbers  of",
                " gamma-quanta  (4pi   Crystall   Ball   spectrometer,",
                " consisting of 160 NaI detectors)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The dipole    responce   of   stable   and   unstable",
                " neutron-rich oxygen nuclei of masses A = 17 to  A  =",
                " 22  has  been  investigated experimentally utilizing",
                " electromagnetic excitation in  heavy-ion  collisions",
                " at   beam   energies   about   600   MeV/nucleon.  A",
                " kinematically complete measurement  of  the  neutron",
                " decay   channel   in  inelastic  scattering  of  the",
                " secondary  beam  projectiles  from  Pb  target   was",
                " performed.  Differential  electromagnetic excitation",
                " cross sections dsig/de were derived  up  to  30  MeV",
                " excitation energy. In contrast to stable nuclei, the",
                " deduced dipole strength distribution appears  to  be",
                " strongly  fragmented  and  systematically exhibits a",
                " considerable fraction of low-lying strength."
              ]
            }
          ],
